#import "../../lib.typ": chapter

#chapter(11, "The sudden entrance of underclasswomen")[
  _"How rare! It's just the second day of the new school year, and there is
  already a girl knocking on our door!"_

  That was what Miyano Koto thought after she heard a voice from the door.
  Putting down the book on anarchist movements during the 15th century, which
  she would recommend to anyone interested in history and how it influenced
  modern society, the girl replied to the knocking with a gentle voice,

  "Come in! The door is unlocked."

  Following her response, the door was opened and three girls enter the
  clubroom. The last girl to enter, who gently closed the door as if trying to
  make the least noise possible, somehow struck Koto as someone really popular.

  _"Was that the rumored Narumi Sena's little sister?"_

  On the first day of the new schoolyear, Koto heard about rumors of a
  celebrity's little sister entering the school, before the news quickly
  exploded on the second day, when Narumi Mona's existence had become public
  knowledge.

  Despite not knowing much about celebrities, people in her class had been
  discussing all sorts of things about Sena and Koto, involuntarily, absorbed
  some information. One thing was that Sena was terrible at studying, especially
  Classical Lit., but somehow her sister was able to enter Misuzu.

  Hence, the fact that Sena's little sister entered the room was quite a weird
  thing to see. Or maybe the information she knew was just nonsense, as how
  things on the Internet all seemed to be blown out of proportion.

  Anyway, she knew that Mona had been receiving much attention from literally
  everyone, so it might make her uncomfortable to treat her as such. She saw a
  few of clubmates throwing glances at Mona, and how she seemed to be worried at
  the glazes she got.

  "Welcome to the Classical Literature Club. Go ahead and take a seat!" Koto
  said with a gentle smile on her smile.

  Things ultimately settled down as the three girls, including Mona, settled
  down to sit at the opposite table as Koto, the only place where three
  consecutive empty seats were available.

  Originally a reserved classroom, the Classical Lit. clubroom had quite a lot
  of old classroom equipments, which was initially moved to one side of the
  room. Though, some desks were utilized to form a big square at the center, to
  form some sorts of reading space that resembled a council chamber rather than
  reading space. Maybe it was used for such purposes sometimes.

  Now that Koto had taken a closer look at her new guests, she realized that
  the Mona girl seemed to be much shyer than her older sister, so maybe she was
  dragged by the other two girls here? Meanwhile, the other two seemed to be
  more sociable, though due to the silent atmosphere of the clubroom, as
  everyone was focused on their own readings, had no intention of making noise.

  She had to take the initiative, it seemed.

  "You girls are here to check out the club, right? If you have any question,
  then feel free to ask me right away! I’m all ears."

  Koto tried to bridge the gap between senior and junior students. By her own
  experience, she knew that this was a huge distance to cover, so she would like
  to make things easier for the three girl by doing so.

  "Thanks" the girls muttered in unison. Though, Mona's voice seemed to not
  reach Koto's ears, which meaned that she was the most shy in her group,
  confirrming Koto's previous suspicion.

  Now that they finally could sit down and observe, the girls finally tried
  to have a quick look at things. The clubroom, despite the eye-catching sign,
  was much ordinary than what they thought. The only things aged-looking were some
  awards hanged on the wall, which seemed to dated from some time after the
  Second World War. The awards were progressively cleaner and more-moderny,
  which seemed to document the whole existence of the club. The newest seemed to
  be "Best Novel Award of Tokyo Classical Novel Fair", awarded to Miyano Koto.

  Seeing the impressive list of awards on the wall, Uta proceeded with a
  question,

  "Senpai, what's the main activities of the club?"

  "Hmm, we mainly read books and take part in writing contests. You see the
  awards and certificates hanging around the place, right? They were all from
  those. Ah! Writing could be hard when you first started, but it would
  gradually become easier, so you girls don’t have to fear. And even if you are
  bad at writing, it’s perfectly okay! Just read more and you will naturally get
  better."

  "Uhm-, I got it. Thank you very much, senpai!" Uta politely replied.

  "If you girls were still hesitant because you don't have any experience in
  writing or you had bad grades in Classical Lit., do not worry" Koto continued,
  "There was this one girl (who wanted to remain anonymous), who almost failed
  every Classical Lit. exams in middle school, ended up getting a Second Prize
  at the prefectural contest."

  Right immediately after Koto finished speaking, something hit her hips.
  There were some giggles in the clubroom, but the girls were too tense to
  notice them.

  The three girls, out of curiosity, looked at the listing of awards to find the
  Second Prize Koto was talking about.

  "Second Prize, Tokyo Novelist Competition, Tsukishima Ako"

  Well, there goes the anonymous part.

  And the girl named Tsukishima Ako was sitting right next to Koto, but the
  girls had not known any names yet. She was the one throwing a punch to Koto's
  hips earlier.

  "Anyone has more questions?" Koto tried to change the topic, after realizing
  her mistake.

  "Me! Senpai, would you be so kind to give us your name?" The brown-hair
  ponytail girl asked with too much politeness.

  The question made Koto realize that she had not introduced herself yet. Koto
  always had to make speeches, so she had perfected her speech to some extent.
  Her self-introduction, however...

  "Me? Well, my name is Miyano Koto. I am the president of the club, hmm... what’s
  next... Ah! My favorite novel genres are romance and historical. Anything more
  you want to know about me?"

  Like a certain someone, Koto was terrible at introducing herself. It was the
  first time she was seen flustered, which, in her favor, made the girls less
  tensed up for a bit.
]
